Utility of functions in R Any process that you find you want to carry out repeatedly can be made into a function In fact, you should make repetitive processes into functions DRY vs WET Code Both acronyms
DRY - &ldquo;Don&rsquo;t Repeat Yourself&rdquo;
DRY (“Don&rsquo;t Repeat Yourself”) principle follows the idea of every logic duplication being eliminated by abstraction. This means that during the development process we should avoid writing repetitive duplicated code as much as possible.
